SPARQL-Galaxy
=============

ABOUT
-----

Execute SPARQL queries against RDF datasets in Galaxy. The query can be pasted or uploaded as a file.


INSTALLATION
------------

1. Stop Galaxy.

2. Download or clone with mercurial (`hg clone http://mikel-egana-aranguren@toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repos/mikel-egana-aranguren/sparql_galaxy`).

3. Copy everything under galaxy-dist/ to your server's galaxy-dist/ (i.e. recreate the tools/ and tool-data/ directories in your server).

4. Add the following lines to your server's /galaxy-dist/tool_conf.xml:

```
  <section name="SPARQL-Galaxy" id="SPARQLGalaxy">
    <tool file="sparql_galaxy/SPARQLGalaxy.xml"/>
  </section>
```
  
5. Start Galaxy.


